{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The SIM-CLDA model [23] applied matrix completion and principal component analysis to infer potential associations.",
    "The NCPLDA model [24] capitalized on the networks consistency projection to obtain a new computational model for calculating new associations between lncRNAs and diseases.",
    "The GrwLDA model [25] generated a global network by combining identified lncRNA-disease interaction information, disease fusion similarity, and lncRNA fusion similarity and utilized this network to explore novel associations between diseases and lncR-NAs.",
    "The LRWRHLDA model [26] integrated multiple heterogeneous and homogeneous networks to construct a three-layer bioinformatics network using RWR to mine interactions.",
    "The LRWHLDA model [27] is designed to excavate the relationships between diseases and lncRNAs with a new idea based on localized random walk that takes full advantage of the topology of the network."
  ],
